                <div class="jonra" data-uuid="c9ffc69543d8470ca2af213131c76633">
                    <h2 data-uuid="456a55527c454117a35bf44bc17de753">Packing the Supreme Court</h2>
                    <p class="source" data-uuid="2e625b00d2864db19df2bd2bd2127bb2">In 1937 Roosevelt’s proposal to add six justices drew heavy criticism. Both Democrats and Republicans in Congress charged that FDR’s plan violated the Constitution. This political cartoon from 1937 similarly conveyed a critical view of court-packing.</p>
                </div>
